originalText.text: This is a small family-run barber shop where the barbers don't speak much English and really only speak Mandarin and Fujianese (and some Cantonese). It might be hard for non-Chinese speakers and I don't think they have a book of haircstyles either (it's best to show them a picture). I've been getting my haircut by these people since I was a child and it's still my go-to barber shop. The prices are incredible at only $8 for a men's cut and $10 for a women's cut (cash only). For first timers I would recommend to show up with an open mind and don't expect things to work like American barber shops.

originalText.text: This became my place to go for a haircut. I lived all the way in new jersey and once in a while when my parents go to Manhattan, I would go get a haircut. I was recommended from a family member and the haircut is pretty good. Nice people.Definitely recommend.
